			<summary>
				<narrativeincludeclinical>The patient started taking the first dose at 6 pm last night, 07/22/14. About 3/4 of the way through the dose she vomited. The product is supposed to have a berry flavor but all the patient could taste was a bitter "product" taste. She can still taste the product in her mouth today. She called her doctor last night after vomiting and he told her to stop taking the product and to cancel the procedure. He also prescribed her Reglan but she was not able to leave the house last night to fill it so she has not taken it. She has Compazine that she takes on a some what regular basis due to an unknown cause of nausea so she tried taking it and it did not help. Her nausea is the reason they are doing the colonoscopy.

07/25/14: The patient is doing fine, but she still cannot get the taste of the product out of her mouth. The patient developed dizziness and a headache when she was vomiting. Symptoms lasted through the night.

CONCOMITANT PRODUCTS AND THERAPY DATES

Protonix, Lisinopril, Celebrex, Cymbalta, Tramadol, Vicodin, Valium, Compazine, Fioricet, Vitamin C, Vitamin D, Flagyl/Amoxicillin</narrativeincludeclinical>
